@startuml approach3-linq-detailed-activity
title **Approach 3: CosmosClient + FakeCosmosHandler — LINQ Query Flow (Detailed)**

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #666

|Setup|
start
:Create **new InMemoryContainer**("orders", "/pk");
:Create **new FakeCosmosHandler**(inMemoryContainer);
:Create **new CosmosClient**(connectionString,
new CosmosClientOptions ~{
  ConnectionMode = Gateway,
  HttpClientFactory = () →
    new HttpClient(handler)
~});

note right
  Connection string is syntactically valid
  but points nowhere — all HTTP requests
  go to FakeCosmosHandler in-process.
end note

#FFF3E0:=== Get Container ===|

|Test Code|
:Call **client.GetContainer**(databaseId, containerId)
→ Container (real SDK proxy —
no HTTP call, lightweight);

#FFF3E0:=== LINQ Expression Building ===|

|CosmosClient (real SDK)|
:Call **container.GetItemLinqQueryable<T>()**;
:SDK creates **CosmosLinqQueryProvider**
(real SDK query provider — NOT LINQ-to-Objects);
:Return **IOrderedQueryable<T>**
(backed by CosmosLinqQueryProvider,
expression tree rooted here);

|Test Code|
:Apply LINQ operators
(builds Expression Tree — no execution):
.**Where**(x => x.Status == "active")
→ MethodCallExpression added
.**OrderBy**(x => x.Name)
→ OrderBy node added
.**Select**(x => new ~{ x.Id, x.Name ~})
→ Select projection added;

note right
  Unlike Approach 1 & 2, these operators
  do NOT execute as C# delegates.
  They build an expression tree that
  the SDK will translate to SQL.
end note

#FFE0B2:=== LINQ-to-SQL Translation ===|

|CosmosClient (real SDK)|
:Call .**ToFeedIterator()**;

note right
  No production code change needed!
  Real .ToFeedIterator() works because
  the queryable is backed by the real
  SDK's CosmosLinqQueryProvider.
  (Unlike Approach 1 & 2 which need
  .ToFeedIteratorOverridable())
end note

:CosmosLinqQueryProvider.**Execute**(expression);

:Visit expression tree nodes:
• WhereExpression → WHERE clause
• OrderByExpression → ORDER BY clause
• SelectExpression → SELECT fields
• Property access → camelCase mapping
• Constants → parameter binding
• Method calls → SQL function mapping
  (e.g. .Contains() → CONTAINS());

:Generate Cosmos SQL:
"SELECT VALUE
  ~{"Id": c.id, "Name": c.name~}
FROM c
WHERE c.status = 'active'
ORDER BY c.name ASC";

:Return **FeedIterator<T>** (SDK pipeline);

#E8F5E9:=== Query Plan Phase (SDK-initiated) ===|

|Test Code|
:Call **ReadNextAsync()** (first call);

|CosmosClient (real SDK)|
:SDK builds **HTTP POST** (query plan request):
**POST** /dbs/~{db~}/colls/~{coll~}/docs
Header: x-ms-cosmos-is-query-plan-request: True
Header: Content-Type: application/query+json
Body: ~{ "query": "SELECT VALUE
    ~{"Id": c.id, "Name": c.name~}
  FROM c WHERE c.status = 'active'
  ORDER BY c.name ASC" ~};

|FakeCosmosHandler|
:**SendAsync**(request);
:Route: detect header
x-ms-cosmos-is-query-plan-request
→ **HandleQueryPlanAsync()**;

|CosmosSqlParser|
:**TryParse**(SDK-generated SQL)
→ CosmosSqlQuery AST:
  SelectFields: [Id, Name] (VALUE projection)
  Where: c.status = 'active'
  OrderBy: [c.name ASC];

|FakeCosmosHandler|
:Analyze AST to build
**PartitionedQueryExecutionInfo**:
• Scan OrderBy → ["Ascending"]
• Scan SELECT for aggregates → []
• Detect DISTINCT → None
• Generate **rewrittenQuery**
  (wraps in orderByItems + payload
  for SDK merge-sort);

:Return **200 OK** with JSON body:
~{
  queryRanges: [~{min:"",max:"FF"~}],
  aggregates: [],
  orderBy: ["Ascending"],
  distinctType: "None",
  rewrittenQuery: "SELECT …"
~};

|CosmosClient (real SDK)|
:Receive query plan;
:Build execution pipeline:
• **OrderByPipelineStage** (ORDER BY c.name)
• AggregatePipelineStage (none)
• DistinctPipelineStage (none);

#C8E6C9:=== Query Execution Phase (per page, per range) ===|

while (SDKIter.HasMoreResults?) is (yes)

  |CosmosClient (real SDK)|
  :SDK builds **HTTP POST** (query request):
  **POST** /dbs/~{db~}/colls/~{coll~}/docs
  Header: x-ms-documentdb-isquery: True
  Header: x-ms-max-item-count: ~{pageSize~}
  Header: x-ms-continuation: ~{token~}
  Header: x-ms-documentdb-query-partitionkeyrangeid: ~{rangeId~}
  Header: Content-Type: application/query+json
  Body: ~{ "query": "… (rewritten
    with orderByItems)",
    "parameters": [~{"name":"@p1","value":"active"~}] ~};

  |FakeCosmosHandler|
  :**SendAsync**(request);
  :Route: detect header
  x-ms-documentdb-isquery: True
  → **HandleQueryAsync()**;

  :Extract from HTTP request:
  • sqlQuery (body JSON .query)
  • partitionKey (header)
  • maxItemCount (header)
  • continuationToken → parse offset
  • rangeId (header);

  :**_queryLog.Add**(sqlQuery)
  (available for test assertions);

  |QueryResultCache|
  :**TryGet**(cacheKey);

  if (cache hit?) then (yes)
    :Return cached results + offset;
  else (no)

    |CosmosSqlParser|
    :**TryParse**(sqlQuery)
    → CosmosSqlQuery AST;

    |FakeCosmosHandler|
    if (ORDER BY detected in AST?) then (yes)

      #FFFDE7:=== ORDER BY Path ===|

      :Call **HandleOrderByQueryAsync()**;

      |CosmosSqlParser|
      :**SimplifySdkQuery**(parsed)
      → strip orderByItems/payload wrapper
      → recover original LINQ-generated SQL:
      "SELECT VALUE
        ~{"Id": c.id, "Name": c.name~}
      FROM c WHERE c.status = 'active'
      ORDER BY c.name ASC";

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :**BuildQueryDefinition**()
      → QueryDefinition with parameters;

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :**GetItemQueryIterator<JObject>**
      (queryDefinition, requestOptions);

      |InMemoryContainer.FilterItemsByQuery|
      :**Parse**(simplifiedSql) → AST;

      :GetAllItemsForPartition()
      → List<string> from store
      (partition-filtered, TTL-applied);

      :AugmentWithComputedProperties();
      :ExpandFromSource();
      :ExpandAllJoins();

      #LightYellow:=== WHERE per item ===
      **EvaluateWhereExpression**
      → **EvaluateSqlExpression** (recursive)
      Evaluates: c.status = 'active'
      → PropertyAccess("c","status")
      → BinaryExpression(=)
      → LiteralExpression("active")
      Full support for 40+ built-in
      functions, subqueries, etc.|

      :ApplyGroupBy() + aggregates;
      :ApplyOrderByFields()
      → sort by c.name ASC;
      :TOP / OFFSET+LIMIT;
      :ProjectFields()
      → SELECT VALUE ~{"Id": c.id, "Name": c.name~};
      :StripComputedProperties();
      :DISTINCT;
      :UnwrapValueSelect()
      → extract VALUE projection;

      :Return List<string> (JSON);

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :Deserialize → List<JObject>;
      :Create InMemoryFeedIterator<JObject>;

      |FakeCosmosHandler.DrainIterator|
      :**DrainIterator<JObject>()**
      → loop ReadNextAsync()
        until !HasMoreResults
      → materialize ALL results
      → List<JToken>;

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :Reconstruct each document:
      ~{
        "orderByItems": [
          ~{"item": "nameValue"~}
        ],
        "payload": ~{
          "Id": "…", "Name": "…"
        ~}
      ~}
      → SDK uses orderByItems
        for cross-partition merge-sort;

    else (no — standard query)

      #E3F2FD:=== Standard Path ===|

      |CosmosSqlParser|
      :**SimplifySdkQuery**(parsed)
      → simplify SDK internal SQL;

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :**BuildQueryDefinition**()
      → QueryDefinition with parameters;

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :**GetItemQueryIterator<JToken>**
      (queryDefinition, requestOptions);

      |InMemoryContainer.FilterItemsByQuery|
      :Parse(sql) → AST;
      :GetAllItemsForPartition();
      :AugmentWithComputedProperties();
      :ExpandFromSource();
      :ExpandAllJoins();

      #LightYellow:WHERE → EvaluateWhereExpression()
      → EvaluateSqlExpression() (recursive)|

      :ApplyGroupBy() + aggregates;
      :ApplyOrderByFields();
      :TOP / OFFSET+LIMIT;
      :ProjectFields();
      :StripComputedProperties();
      :DISTINCT;
      :UnwrapValueSelect();
      :Return List<string>;

      |InMemoryContainer|
      :Deserialize → List<JToken>;
      :Create InMemoryFeedIterator<JToken>;

      |FakeCosmosHandler.DrainIterator|
      :**DrainIterator<JToken>()**
      → materialize all results;

      |FakeCosmosHandler|
      :Wrap aggregates for SDK if needed:
      • AVG → ~{"sum": val, "count": 1~}
      • COUNT → ~{"$1": n~}
      • SUM/MIN/MAX → ~{"$1": val~};

    endif

    |FakeCosmosHandler|
    :**FilterDocumentsByRange**
    (documents, rangeId, payloadPropertyName)
    → hash each doc's partition key
    → keep only docs in this range;

    |QueryResultCache|
    :**Set**(cacheKey, allDocuments)
    TTL from CacheTtl (default 5 min);

  endif

  |FakeCosmosHandler|
  :**BuildPagedResponse**()
  → Skip(offset).Take(maxItemCount)
  → continuation token (offset-based)
  → Serialize JSON:
    ~{ "_rid": "collRid",
      "Documents": [ …page… ],
      "_count": n ~};

  :Set response headers:
  • x-ms-request-charge: 1
  • x-ms-activity-id: ~{guid~}
  • x-ms-session-token: 0:0#1
  • x-ms-item-count: ~{count~}
  • x-ms-continuation: ~{token|null~};

  :Return **HttpResponseMessage** (200 OK);

  |CosmosClient (real SDK)|
  :SDK pipeline stages process response:
  • OrderByPipelineStage reads orderByItems,
    merge-sorts across partition ranges
  • AggregatePipelineStage accumulates
  • Deserialize JSON → T;

  :Create **FeedResponse<T>**;

  |Test Code|
  :Receive **FeedResponse<T>**;

endwhile (no)

note right
  **Key difference from Approach 1 & 2:**
  LINQ expressions are translated to SQL
  by the real SDK's CosmosLinqQueryProvider,
  then executed through CosmosSqlParser —
  testing the full LINQ → SQL → HTTP →
  parse → execute → serialize pipeline.

  .ToFeedIterator() works unchanged
  (no .ToFeedIteratorOverridable() needed).
end note

stop

@enduml
